The cold snap is not expected to impact much on Gauteng and other interior provinces. JOHANNESBURG - The SA Weather Service is warning a cold front is expected to hit the Western Cape on Wednesday.It says although temperatures will start dropping later on Tuesday night.The cold snap is not expected to impact much on Gauteng and other interior provinces.Western Cape Tomorrow 's Weather overview: 24.5.2017 pic.twitter.com/SS0y4oGlMGForecaster Mbavhi Maliage said: We re expecting a very weak cold front to slip south of the country on Wednesday. It will only affect the Cape Town area. It will cause a cooling, especially around the coast. The only places that we re expecting rainfall is the extreme south-western part of the Western Cape. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)